RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $1,650 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOVERNOR ANN was well rated while tracking the pace in the two path, bid on the second turn, dug in gamely in the early stretch to edge clear in the late stretch and was up just in time to succeed. MORE THAN SHAKIN lead the way into the first turn while resisting rating until about the half pole, then made bid throughout the second turn, menaced in the home stretch but was out kicked in the end by an outer and was second best. RIVER'S END was forwardly place along the inside, was in a steady drive down the backstretch and into the turn to rally in the upper stretch then flattened out in the end. MYRTLE BEACH raced behind rivals while four wide on the backstretch then bid from the inside on the far turn but came up evenly throughout the lane. RON'S LAVENDER was off slowly at the start, sped through the first turn swiftly then gradually faded throughout the second half of the course and was through early.

ENTRY.NAME: Myrtle Beach
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4 wide backstretch, bid inside turn, even throughout

ENTRY.NAME: Ron's Lavender
ENTRY.COMMENT: stayed in gate, brief speed 1st turn, faded, through early

ENTRY.NAME: River's End
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, steady drive, rallied upper, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: More Than Shakin
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace 2 wide, long drive, out finished late

ENTRY.NAME: Governor Ann
ENTRY.COMMENT: track 2 wide, well rated, bid far turn, gamely, edge clear late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 13500. (PLUS UP TO $2,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 27, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARBON STRYKER slow away in the first strides, rushed up between horses to duel for the lead from two wide, took command at the top of the lane and steadily drew clear down the stretch as a convincing winner. DAAHERS BULLY reserved along the fence off the early leaders, angled out turning for home and closed well to be a clear second best. PLAY RULE broke alertly to sprint to the early lead, dueled with the winner through the turn and flattened out in the drive. SHANGHAI'S DREAM trailed into the lane while wide throughout and passed a tired rival late. MAGIC BOW tracked the leaders in striking position but could not sustain his bid while tiring late.

ENTRY.NAME: Daahers Bully
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, closed well, late gain for place

ENTRY.NAME: Play Rule
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly, dueled lead, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Carbon Stryker
ENTRY.COMMENT: slow start, dueled, took command, drew clear, convincing

ENTRY.NAME: Magic Bow
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked, striking position, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Shanghai's Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, wide, passed tired rival

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 23000. (PLUS UP TO $4,600 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 27, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISTER K dueled from the inside into the turn, took the lead in the upper stretch, was challenged for command in the late stretch by an outer rival, but held onto the lead grudgingly by a nose in the end to prove best. PICKNNGRINN chased the dueling leaders while two wide, then vied for the lead heading into the stretch, shook clear of one rival, menaced gamely to duel with an inner rival in late stretch but hung in the end. SR. BI BI chased the pace along the inside, bid mildly on the turn then rallied in the late stretch but came up empty. BEHIND THE CURTAIN dueled for the lead while two wide, lead the way into the turn by a nose, then vied to keep the lead in the early stretch but was depleted and gave way in the end.

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled inside, gamely upper, dueled again late, held grudgingly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 74. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $6,700 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on them ain track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILD EXPRESS broke alertly to take the lead from the gate, opened a comfortable, well-rated lead down the backside in soft fractions, responded well when threatened turning for home and drew clear in a well handled ride. TRIPLE L'S CUTTER tracked the pace from the rail always in striking distance, angled off the rail at the top of the lane, and closed well to be second best. CRAFTY MONEY stalked the pacesetter throughout, loomed up at the quarter pole to threaten but failed to gain on the leader in the stretch. OH DOO DAH DAY broke a step slow, circled three wide in the first turn while fighting the rider under a strong hold, moved up in the far turn to challenge and flattened out in the drive. DASHYNS DREAM was well placed in striking distance of the leaders to the three-eighths pole and finished evenly. CHA CHA DANCER trailed throughout and was never a threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $3,000 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUMMEROSA chased the pace while three wide, was moving up heading into the far turn to rally in the early stretch, dueled with the pace setter then kicked clear in deep stretch to prove best in the end. JAZZY LASSIE lead the way into the first turn to duel down the backstretch from the inside, shook clear of that rival at the top of the far turn to lead the way again into the early stretch, was confronted by an outer rival in the late stretch and could not retain rally and gave way in the end. MUCHO MAMA MIA raced behind most of the field while two wide on the backstretch, then made a strong bid on the far turn to rally in the early stretch and was closing well but it wasn't enough in the end. SUPERCENTS was under a steady ride while three wide down the backstretch, then bid on the far turn to rally in stretch and was closing well but came up empty in the end. SIGNE was forwardly placed while two wide into the first turn to duel with an inner foe down the backstretch, was in a hard drive throughout the far turn, was used up and weakened in the home stretch. TALKATIVE was bumped at the start, then raced in the middle of the field along the inside, made a mild bid heading into the far turn then flattened out in the stretch. JOHNBOYS JENNY was unhurried early, bid on the second turn and was no threat. GOLD MAKIN GIRL bumped rival at the start, then tracked the pace between rivals down the backstretch, faded throughout the far turn and had no final bid in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO $2,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500. Texas Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT HUNTER sped up the fence to duel on the early lead, opened a slight advantage to the top of the lane and drew off as much the best. PRATHER stalked the pacesetters from three wide to the quarter pole, mounted a challenge turning for home but was no match for the winner while holding on gamely for the place. MORO'S BULL CREEK tracked the leaders while well positioned, angled out at the head of the stretch and rallied well on the outside to just miss the place. WINNY'SSPECIALSTAR pressed the winner while dueling for the first quarter, maintained that position until the head of the lane and flattened out late in the drive. FEW WORDS raced three wide into the turn near the rear of the pack and made a mild gain down the stretch. CAPO'S DREAM trailed to the quarter pole and passed tired rivals in the lane. IFFY ASSET CLASS was in contention early, dropped back through the turn lacking a rally and finished evenly as no threat. BLACKHEATH broke mid-pack, dropped to the rail entering the turn, was put to an early drive but failed to respond to his rider's urging, and faded to the wire.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, late wide gain, missed place

ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, late interest, passed tiring rivals

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, dueled, flattened out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 7 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 96. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $6,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 27, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 27, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG COUNTRY was well rated while two wide down the backstretch and into the far turn, then bid gamely in the early stretch, dueled with an inner foe in the final sixteenth and was up in the final strides to prove best. BIG BERNIE showed the way into the first turn and down the backstretch, continued to hold onto the lead gamely while heading into the home stretch, was confronted by an outer rival in the final furlong and was out finished in the end. HAMAZING WISDOM was rated in the two path down the heading down the backstretch, was urging steadily on the far turn to rally gamely at the top of the stretch and was closing well and was best for show. SINGING DIXIE was under a strong drive to press the pace down the backstretch and into the far turn, rallied in the early stretch but did not fire in the end. OPTIMAL TRIP raced along the rail down the first half then came out three wide on the far turn to rally in the early stretch but came up evenly. EXETER tracked the pace while three deep down the backstretch, was in hard drive on the far turn then flattened out in the lane and was no threat. CANATLAN was unhurried early then trailed behind the field down the backstretch, bid from the three path on the far turn and was no factor. MANOR BORN raced behind the field while two wide, then steadily lost ground and had no final bid in the stretch.
